{
  "texts": [
    "Observe however that the expected fraction of u.a.r.",
    "training subsets that either contains all instances in a group or none of a group decays geometrically with m n and (1 -m n), respectively.",
    "Therefore, for large group sizes, K needs to be exponential in n to cover sufficient group combinations.",
    "Remark 5 Downsampling trains models on data subsets of size m under the assumption that statements made about those models generalize to models trained on a dataset of size n (i.e., all of D).",
    "This assumption may not hold for small m."
  ]
}